This paper deals with the complexity and expressive power of conjunctive queries over trees, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper focuses on query evaluation and expressiveness. The second likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with the representation and manipulation of trees. The third likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper uses logical formalisms to study the complexity and expressive power of queries. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with the representation and manipulation of structured data, which is relevant to several AI applications. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), as the paper deals with the expressive power of formal languages for representing trees.
